    The range of values (from start to end) under which an Eff is valid; the start value is required, and indicates when the Eff becomes valid, but the end value is optional, and when non-null signifies when an Eff is no longer valid.

Package wt.eff Description

Provides generic base effectivity functionality via EffService to assert that a PDM object is effective under certain conditions. The EffRecordable provides a plug-and-play interface to store effectivity information for objects. An EffRecordable object manages any number of effectivities.

When manufacturing a product it is necessary to specify which versions of parts are used to produce the product. From the standpoint of a version we say that the version is effective in some context (usually the specific product being manufactured) when manufactured within a specific range of dates, serial numbers or lot numbers. Often a configuration specification is used to simplify retrieving all the versions that are needed for a product.

Key classes from this package implementing the concept of effectivity:

  • For Versioned Object: EffManagedVersion
  • For Non-Versioned Object: EffRecordable
  • Effectivity: Eff
    • DateEff
    • StringEff
    • LeftFilledStringEff
  • Range: EffRange
    • DateEffRange
    • StringEffRange
    • LeftFilledStringEffRange
  • Group of Effs: EffGroup (used as a convenience in the UI)
